was getting married.

00:37:58.240 --> 00:38:03.160
And my agent at that point
had called me, and he said,

00:38:03.160 --> 00:38:05.374
[NON-ENGLISH] picture,
[NON-ENGLISH].

00:38:05.374 --> 00:38:06.482
Like that.

00:38:06.482 --> 00:38:08.940
And I had never had a hit film,
so for me, it was like, oh,

00:38:08.940 --> 00:38:09.439
good.

00:38:09.439 --> 00:38:10.781
I have a hit film now.

00:38:10.781 --> 00:38:11.280
It's a hit.

00:38:11.280 --> 00:38:12.470
It's a success.

00:38:12.470 --> 00:38:15.640
And so I was very
happy about that,

00:38:15.640 --> 00:38:19.360
but I'd never faced recognition
before when I was working.

00:38:19.360 --> 00:38:20.962
Oh, once in awhile, maybe.

00:38:20.962 --> 00:38:22.712
But I had landed at
the airport, and there

00:38:22.712 --> 00:38:24.370
was these two little
kids, you know,

00:38:24.370 --> 00:38:27.350
who come in and kind of
wipe your car sometimes.

00:38:27.350 --> 00:38:31.090
