00:39:22.570 --> 00:39:25.660
So how would Dance with
Madhuri help, and what advice

00:39:25.660 --> 00:39:27.190
do you have for people like me?

00:39:27.190 --> 00:39:29.023
MADHURI DIXIT-NENE:
Well, Dance with Madhuri

00:39:29.023 --> 00:39:31.730
is something you can do in your
own time, in your own space.

00:39:31.730 --> 00:39:34.190
You could be in your own
room in front of a computer.

00:39:34.190 --> 00:39:35.910
Nobody's watching you.

00:39:35.910 --> 00:39:39.140
And it's just the teacher
in front of you and you.

00:39:39.140 --> 00:39:42.300
And I think somewhere it'll
help you get away inhibitions,

00:39:42.300 --> 00:39:44.460
because nobody's
watching you do that.

00:39:44.460 --> 00:39:47.756
And with Dance with Madhuri,
you can rewind it 20,000 times

00:39:47.756 --> 00:39:49.380
and see it again,
and again, and again,

00:39:49.380 --> 00:39:51.334
which a school
doesn't afford you.

00:39:51.334 --> 00:39:53.750
Because once you go there, the
class is just for one hour.

00:39:53.750 --> 00:39:56.430
You come home, and you
have to basically work

00:39:56.430 --> 00:39:59.810
where your memory-- you know,
wherever your memory is good,

00:39:59.810 --> 00:40:01.490
that's what you will remember.

00:40:01.490 --> 00:40:04.310
But with this, you can
practice in your own time,

00:40:04.310 --> 00:40:05.320
in your own space.

00:40:05.320 --> 00:40:11.730
And every little lesson is
split into 15-seconders.

00:40:11.730 --> 00:40:14.220
So they will teach you
step-by-step every little

00:40:14.220 --> 00:40:15.010
thing.

00:40:15.010 --> 00:40:17.269
And I think it'll be
easier to learn that way.

00:40:17.269 --> 00:40:17.810
